-- Whiskey Maker Ravi Kumar Distilleries Advances 25% in Mumbai Trading Debut
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2010-12-27T12:10:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/ravi-kumar-distilleries-advances-as-much-as-34-in-mumbai-trading-debut.html
Ravi Kumar Distilleries Ltd. , an
Indian maker of alcoholic beverages, climbed 25 percent in its
Mumbai trading debut after its initial public offer received
demand for 2.2 times the shares on sale.  The stock  rose  to 80.05 rupees at the 3:30 p.m. close of
trading in Mumbai. The shares surged as much as 42 percent to 91
rupees earlier. The company based in the southern city of
Puducherry raised 736 million rupees ($16.3 million) selling
shares at 64 rupees each in an IPO earlier this month.  Ravi Kumar, which makes and sells whiskey, rum, gin and
vodka, will use the proceeds to expand distillation capacity,
finance development of its brands and meet working capital needs,
the company said in its sale document.  Ravi Kumar posted a profit of 19.9 million rupees on sales
of 502 million rupees in the year ended March 31. The companyâ€™s
promoters own a 52 percent stake after the issue.  To contact the reporters on this story:
